main event: An unidentified object was sighted in Marietta, Georgia on January 25, 1957, described as a clear-shaped object traveling at high speed.
interesting points: The object was reported to be 25 to 30 ft long with bright flames of light on the front and back,The observation lasted for 30 to 40 seconds,There was one object observed,The report suggests the observer might have been influenced by previous sightings,Another report mentioned a potential meteor sighting in Marietta, GA.
witness description: civilian, likely influenced by reports of sightings
